        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 12:21AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1221 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rougemont, or 10 miles northeast of Hillsborough, moving southeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Durham, Creedmoor, Butner, Rougemont, Stem, Lake Michie, Falls Lake
State Rec Area, Eno River State Park, Gorman, and Bahama.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
